title: Goldman Sachs is cutting jobs again amid Wall Street deals slump
description: Goldman Sachs, more tied to the ups and downs of Wall Street than its rivals, is cutting jobs again.

title: ChatGPT cited 'bogus' cases for a New York federal court filing. The attorneys involved may face sanctions.
description: A pair of New York attorneys used ChatGPT to generate a legal motion they filed in New York federal court, which has now put them at the risk of sanctions.

title: Sen. Tim Scott pushes bill that would require disclosure of apps' country of origin
description: Scott has previously called for the U.S. to cut ties between TikTok and China-based parent company ByteDance.

title: Theranos founder Elizabeth Holmes reports to prison to begin sentence
description: Disgraced Theranos CEO Elizabeth Holmes reported to prison Tuesday to begin her sentence.

title: Arnold Schwarzenegger: 'No one gives a s--- about' climate change — this is what it should be called instead
description: "As long as they keep talking about global climate change, they are not gonna go anywhere. 'Cause no one gives a s--- about that," Arnold Schwarzenegger says.

title: Stocks making the biggest moves midday: Nvidia, Tesla, Coinbase and more
description: These are the stocks posting the largest moves in midday trading.

title: Debt ceiling bill faces a tough path in the House as GOP opposition grows
description: The Fiscal Responsibility Act represents a compromise reached by House Speaker Kevin McCarthy and President Joe Biden. But conservatives say it's a raw deal.

title: Stablecoin giant Tether to mine bitcoin in Uruguay using renewable energy
description: Stablecoin firm Tether said Tuesday it plans to invest its resources into renewable energy production, marking the company's first foray into the energy sector.

title: Nvidia on track to hit $1 trillion market cap when market opens
description: Nvidia is on track to hit a $1 trillion market cap at the market open Tuesday, buoyed by an AI frenzy and a massive earnings beat.

title: Elon Musk meets China's foreign minister as Tesla boss touts expansion in the country
description: The meeting between Tesla CEO Elon Musk and Chinese foreign minster Qin Gang comes as tensions between the U.S. and China continue to rise.

title: China's disappointing rebound could bring in more stimulus, economists say
description: China's much-vaunted economic rebound after its emergence from strict zero-Covid lockdown measures has yet to fully materialize.

title: North Korea says it will launch its first-ever military spy satellite to monitor U.S. drills
description: Pyongyang plans to launch a satellite with the aim to track "dangerous" actions by the U.S., pointing to its recent joint military drills taking with South Korea.

title: China launches crewed mission to its space station
description: A CMSA official said China aims to launch a crewed mission to the moon by 2030, according to state media.

title: 'Everyone is a programmer' with generative A.I., says Nvidia chief
description: "We have closed the digital divide. Everyone is a programmer," says Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang who introduced a new AI supercomputer platform called DGX GH200.

title: Turkish lira continues slide to new record lows following Erdogan's election victory
description: The Turkish lira slumped to fresh all-time lows Tuesday, extending its slide to record lows after Erdogan's re-election.

title: Wall Street sees further upside for Japan stocks as they notch a fresh three-decade high
description: Japan's Topix (Tokyo Price Index) has marked new peaks in the past two weeks, seeing its highest level since July 1990 on Monday.

title: CNBC Daily Open: Next stop, Congress
description: The wrangling on Capitol Hill is not over yet.
